bio:
I am a passionate Software Engineer with 3 years of experience in developing scalable cloud solutions based on microservice architecture and event-driven communication. My expertise lies in designing, building, and optimizing backend systems that are both reliable and efficient. I independently handle technically complex tasks, from gathering requirements to delivering production-ready solutions, all while maintaining a strong focus on performance and scalability.

I'm always eager to stay on top of industry trends and continuously improve my skills, taking on new challenges with curiosity and enthusiasm.

name: Bulatüíª Gabdrakhmanov
headline: Backend Developer, 6+ years, C#, Python, Distributed Systems, web3
creator: False
bio:
I am a C# developer with 6+ years of experience designing and delivering scalable, high-performance systems. I specialize in backend development, cloud solutions, and modern software architectures, creating secure and efficient applications across various industries.

With a proven track record of managing the full development lifecycle, I excel in designing and optimizing APIs and microservices, building cloud-based solutions on AWS and Azure, and implementing CI/CD pipelines. I have extensive experience in both SQL and NoSQL databases, and have worked with Web3 technologies, including blockchain, smart contracts, and NFT marketplaces.

Key Highlights:

- Built and optimized scalable backend system handling up to 1000 requests per second
- Designed and implemented cloud-native solutions on AWS using Lambda, API Gateway, S3, and CloudFormation, optimizing scalability and performance
- Developed decentralized applications (dApps) on Avalanche, enabling secure and transparent interactions
- Improved team efficiency by automating CI/CD pipelines, reducing post-release incidents by 40%
- Mentored junior developers and streamlined cross-functional collaboration for faster feature delivery

In my spare time, I am deeply passionate about blockchain technology, DePIN projects, and crypto trading. I continuously explore the latest developments in these areas to stay ahead of the curve.

I am currently open to remote opportunities and relocation for the right role. Currently based in the GMT+3 time zone.

name: Khush P.
headline: AI/ML & NLP Practitioner | ‚öôÔ∏èMLops
creator: False
bio:
I‚Äôve always been the kind of person who just has to know how things work. As a kid, I‚Äôd pull apart anything that caught my eye‚Äî cars, TV remotes, you name it‚Äîjust to figure out what made them tick. That curiosity naturally led me to a degree in CS, where I majored in Data Science and Applied Artificial Intelligence.

Since then, I‚Äôve thrown myself into a mix of projects, from experimenting with Arduino to building machine learning models. I‚Äôve explored NLP, reinforcement learning, and analytics‚Äîconstantly looking for the next thing to tinker with.

Even now, I‚Äôm still that curious kid at heart‚Äîexcited to break things down, build them back up, and discover something new along the way.

Focus Areas: AI/ML, NLP, MLOps, Software Engineering, Analytics

name: Anastasia Reprintseva üá∫üá¶
headline: Product-Minded Web Engineer at Trade Republic
creator: False
bio:
I'm a Web Engineer based in Berlin, bringing product thinking and technical expertise to Trade Republic. Currently, I'm working on exciting products that will transform how people interact with financial markets.

My engineering approach is deeply rooted in understanding user needs and business context. I believe the best technical solutions come from close collaboration with product teams and users, and I love contributing beyond just writing code ‚Äì from generating product ideas to improving team processes.

I started my frontend journey in 2019, working with React, Angular, and modern web technologies. Along the way, I've had the privilege of leading development teams and mentoring other engineers. One of my proudest achievements was adapting KazanExpress's product for international markets, which taught me valuable lessons about building for global audiences.

Learning is my superpower ‚Äì I'm constantly exploring new technologies and approaches to craft better user experiences. Originally from Ukraine, I now call Berlin home and am excited to be part of its vibrant tech community.
